<subSubSection id="A9CCFC3604CC26EBF780D61352AD28A5" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph id="7C30B865FB44F9A42377E4683EA13E09" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="110F90015C31DD350EB2858FF52EEC88" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
Body length: male 8.1 mm (
<emphasis id="617E702ACAD9C2F4B636823221AB776A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 1), female 8.9-9.3 mm (
<emphasis id="CEDA23AEE2F957222B405A10EAD12DF6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 2); forewing length: male 7.3 mm (
<emphasis id="B6BEE7AF57DA0892D822FF46717E886D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 1), female 7.3-7.9 mm (
<emphasis id="2C0162BB0526FA8ADD77ED3361294E5C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 2); width between humeral angles apices: male 3.3 mm (
<emphasis id="7BA5B2C732185797643BE49A111DA722" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 1), female 3.5-3.8 mm (
<emphasis id="49F0A2C80ECBD26EFAAC76C6B0FB6FCD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 2); width between suprahumeral horns apices: male 4.6 mm (
<emphasis id="A136BCCDE2AD000332FE31D31E1CB3B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 1), female 4.6-5.2 mm (
<emphasis id="40FAD9E27A6F9C66C455B0594ABEAF63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">N</emphasis>
= 2).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D977051322E3BA265F82071F933857D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="A4B40358E5AF523642750B9AF883FA03" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="FBB59653CBC5A8A1566FB651FADF2929" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Coloration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B689C0CA10380844E587476BA5FDC8A" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
General color black with scattered yellow setae. Eyes pale brown with yellow border in males, pale yellow with black markings in females (
<figureCitation id="C701160445ED6ED723A2A4CE98A59A8D" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 1 female habitus, dorsal view 2 same, lateral view 3 male habitus, dorsal view 4 same, lateral view 5 head and pronotum anterior view, female 6 head and pronotum anterior view, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352858" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6">Figs 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F59A1F500FC7FBB70AA617FAC23FF054" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 1 female habitus, dorsal view 2 same, lateral view 3 male habitus, dorsal view 4 same, lateral view 5 head and pronotum anterior view, female 6 head and pronotum anterior view, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352858" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6">6</figureCitation>
), ocelli yellow hyaline. Basal one-third of scutellum dark brown, covered with yellowish-white setae, preapical region yellowish-brown with apical white. Forewing pale yellow hyaline, one-fifth of basal, veins and apical limbus black. Hindwing veins pale brown. Thorax black with pale yellowish pubescence; coxae black with yellow pubescence; trochanter, femur, tibia and tarsus yellowish-brown and tarsal claw dark brown. Abdomen reddish-brown with yellow pubescence, basal part of abdomen with a yellow spot of pubescence, apices of terga and sterna pale yellowish.
</paragraph>
<caption id="F2A3AD414D70C3F5C5CDE8F85432C532" doi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352858" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" start="Figures 1–6" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="278BE993ECE81D68F47F237CA0DD6F80" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="04CC5B63A018B3C5A0F671108CB1DCB8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Figures 1-6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="9BF811D2EDE5BB261535BCD86AC8506D" authority="Yuan, 2002" authorityName="Yuan" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Membracidae" genus="Sinocentrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sinocentrus brevicornis" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis id="9F5E43ADCCF4294783B9DB73902C69BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Sinocentrus brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="557FB46C8EDEFC9898B366C0561FA4E0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">1</emphasis>
female habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="3FE3A07A55DEF8F911F5540510D97747" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">2</emphasis>
same, lateral view 
<emphasis id="8159D5E49A517559053C37056B809B0A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">3</emphasis>
male habitus, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="E2A615DAACCBB7C064E6D8212F654793" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">4</emphasis>
same, lateral view 
<emphasis id="E5B5117D5FFD39F8963F1DDF07651569" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">5</emphasis>
head and pronotum anterior view, female 
<emphasis id="2896AE49098FA9D945D53B1281B608B1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">6</emphasis>
head and pronotum anterior view, male. Scale bars: 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="FDE54CAB92BA32FAFB9123503045C728" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="7F990B21A71D3E95C929355714DCF085" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="46711CB097A8EC9466C7AB214176CA6B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Head and thorax</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head in anterior view wider than long, ratio: 2.11:1. Vertex with dorsal and ventral margins slightly arcuated and wave-shaped respectively, with wrinkles on surface and a weak median longitudinal carina. Eyes and ocelli oval, ocelli slightly closer to inner margins of eyes less than to each other. Frontoclypeus distinct and trilobed, margin with sparse setae, apices of lateral and median lobes on same plane, more than half of median lobe extending beyond towards ventral margin of vertex, and apex dorsally slightly upturned. Apex of metopidium convex in anterior view. Posterior pronotal process ending at more than half of forewing cell M3+4 (last apical cell). Humeral angles triangular with apices somewhat blunt. Suprahumeral horns short, width between horns apices nearly half length of body. Scutellum humped basally, large punctures present, longer than wide, apex extended antero-dorsally male, curved ventrally in female (
<figureCitation id="D2F87F531C7E326F213D9EA9C24B5E91" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 1 female habitus, dorsal view 2 same, lateral view 3 male habitus, dorsal view 4 same, lateral view 5 head and pronotum anterior view, female 6 head and pronotum anterior view, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352858" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BE577D14C8FE57CB5444EBA2A3211963" captionStart="Figures 1–6" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 6. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 1 female habitus, dorsal view 2 same, lateral view 3 male habitus, dorsal view 4 same, lateral view 5 head and pronotum anterior view, female 6 head and pronotum anterior view, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352858" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures1-6">4</figureCitation>
), posterior margin deeply emarginate. Mesothoracic femur without ablateral and adlateral cucullate setae. Metathoracic leg cucullate setae row II irregular.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40814902A8CA7548EC10AEBA2A4B0757" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="6A5360AC5B1A53B9E38EE33B939AADC3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="40C43D2FABE1E3C9DCE8E8184F1DB8EC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="135">Male genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="F23247D68FCAA0D0B84DE3AC476891D5" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1EDAFF5BF36BB70F8B4CA6249ABECC53" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">11</figureCitation>
) nearly trapezoidal in lateral view; sternite IX (
<figureCitation id="5D95FB6E48F3419A2258D4D9C77B36A2" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) depressed medially in ventral view. Anal tube cylindrical-shaped in lateral view. Lateral plate (
<figureCitation id="945621B8CC9ADAB26AE96AFF9D94BFDC" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Figs 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="C009E7DF6572207EE74A03B71B547055" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">11</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="316FC1715298931878DB2BD87748CC9F" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">15</figureCitation>
) with membranous dorsoapical lobe extending dorsally, slightly arcuate with setae; part of other surface with setae, margin incurved in posterior view. Basal half of subgenital plates fused, apex acute, obliquely truncate, distributed evenly setae in ventral view (
<figureCitation id="6CCA751FA7E6A145E7CE6533BB04D617" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). Style (
<figureCitation id="41D33CEF1E31EF6D832D4690DA0BC78F" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Figs 16</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A2C10D0D8BF0BB1D882982AE5A25E8D9" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">17</figureCitation>
) clasp oriented laterally, one-third compressed apically, weakly angled ventrally, lateral surface with setae; style shank with arch at central section. Base of connective W-shaped, distal part membranous and weakly depressed. Aedeagus in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="89D4936BEC76EF7BF4707C35ED752400" captionStart="Figures 7–17" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 7 - 17. Sinocentrus brevicornis Li &amp; Chen, sp. nov. 7 male genitalia, lateral view 8 aedeagus, posterior view 9 aedeagus, lateral view 10 male genitalia, dorsal view 11 male genitalia, posterior view 12 male genitalia, ventral view 13 forewing 14 hindwing 15 lateral plate 16 style, right lateral view 17 style, dorsal view. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (7 - 12, 15 - 17), 1 mm (13 - 14)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/352859" pageId="0" pageNumber="135" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.886.36672.figures7-17">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) nearly C-shaped, apical four-fifths of surface and margin with reverse serrations, the opening at middle-upper of aedeagus, ovoid.
</paragraph>
